<br>
George Washington: Great leader and bringer of freedom, also a married man who was a womanizer and hired whores pretty frequently (well that covers all the founding fathers right there they were all pretty much the same)<br>
<br>
JFK: We already know the good and bad of him<br>
<br>
Abraham Lincoln: Great leader, father of the immancipation proclomation, and a slave owner<br>
<br>
Elvis: Now here's a hero, we go to war and he is drafted, being a media darling he had the option to go to some nowhere post nice and safe, he Demanded instead to go the front and fought along side everyone else.... We all know what happened later with his drugs and the aliens.<br>
<br>
<br>
Everyone has their skeletons, everyone makes mistakes and some screw up big time.  Humans make mistakes.  It's all in how you remember them that matters.  If their minor transgressions against basic morales, which everyone falls to, is to big of a deal for you to handle, was he really a hero in your eyes then?  If he had been a true hero to you you should have been able to say &quot;Everyone makes mistakes, the important thing is learning from them unless they are big ass mistakes like hacking up your ex&quot;.  It's all in your opinion, and history has a tendency to forget about the minor inadequecies of the human condition.  It's all in how you view them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=villagereaver>villagereaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/03 11:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=195.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> my hero</span><hr size=1> Heros: Run INTO the burning building, chase the fleeing felony suspect into a darkened alley without backup, and perform emergency medical care on the sick and injured<br>
