<br>
My heroes are Harry Chapin and Winston Churchill. They both have their darkside, but it doesn't take away from the things they did. Harry Chapin started World Hunger Year (long before &quot;Feed The World&quot; btw) and over half of his shows every year were for that and his other charities. Winston, well, we all know he basically took his voice and persona to war and saved Western Civilization.<br>
